[SN]TITLE[SN]
Kidnap charge over Ashtead pensioner cash withdrawal

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been charged with kidnapping a pensioner who reported being taken to withdraw money against her will.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The woman in her 80s and from Ashtead in Surrey said she had been taken to a cash machine.
The offences were reported on Tuesday, Surrey Police said.
A 32-year-old man of no fixed address has been charged with kidnap and fraud and remanded in custody. He is due to appear at South East Surrey Magistrates' Court on 24 April.
